        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 5 at 6:12PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 612 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Williamstown, or 7 miles west of North Adams, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hairpin Turn, Greylock, North Adams, Sweets Corner, New Ashford,
Soldiers Memorial Field, North Hancock, Cheshire Harbor, Arnoldville,
Savoy, Town Crest Village, Maple Grove, Eastern Summit, Braytonville,
Zylonite, Bowens Corners, Cole Field, Meadowvale, White Oaks, and
Whitcomb Summit.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
